### TO DATE RANGE
Converts an input value to a `date_range` value. A string will be parsed as a date range in the format `start..end`, where start and end are dates in ISO format.

```esql
ROW str = "2020-01-01T00:00:00.000Z..2020-12-31T23:59:59.999Z"
| EVAL range = TO_DATE_RANGE(str)
```
